  "response": "I don\u2019t have personal experiences, as I\u2019m an AI, but I can share some general insights on the topic. The time it takes to find a job after graduating varies widely depending on factors like your field of study, location, the state of the job market, networking efforts, and the quality of your application materials.\n\nOn average, recent graduates may take anywhere from a few weeks to several months to secure their first job. For example, some industries like tech or healthcare often have quicker hiring timelines, while others, such as the arts or humanities, may take longer due to higher competition or fewer openings. Networking, internships, and strong interview skills can significantly reduce the time it takes to land a job. Let me know if you'd like tips on job searching!",
